# HALOS — Spec-Implementing Agent

The HALOS contract (`.cursor/rules/halos-alignment.mdc`) governs all agent behavior. This rule adds **spec-implementing mechanics** when working on the framework, spec, or proposals.

---

## Repo Operations (when changing scripts, Docker, CI, or publishing)

When changing scripts, Docker, CI, or publishing flow, follow `.cursor/rules/halos-repo-operations.mdc` for operating instructions.

---

## Spec Conformance (when editing spec/)

When editing `spec/`, follow `.cursor/rules/halos-spec-conformance.mdc`:

- Use `spec/schema/` for validation; do not violate schemas.
- After editing `core.json`, `manifest.json`, or `changelog.json`, run `node scripts/generate-spec.js` and commit generated `spec.md` and `CHANGELOG.md`.
- Substantive changes go through the proposal process.

---

The HALOS contract applies to every interaction. This rule adds the framework mechanics for spec and proposal work.
